JAPANESE ENCEPHALITIS - INDIA (ANDHRA PRADESH) (03)
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Japanese encephalitis - India (Uttar Pradesh), Nepal 990916214717
Japanese encephalitis - India (Andhra Pradesh) 991115222826
Japanese encephalitis - India (Andhra Pradesh) (02) 991119080535
Date: Sat, 20 Nov 1999 15:44:26 -0500
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: News media, 20 Nov 1999

An outbreak of Japanese encephalitis has killed 133 people, all of them
children, in the southern Indian state of Andhra Pradesh, health officials
said after reporting 10 new deaths. The state's director of health said in
a statement that 38 new cases of the brain disease were reported on
Saturday, taking the total number of cases to 650 in the past two months.
"The situation is being closely monitored," health director K.S.V. Prasada
Rao said. As many as 479 villages in 10 districts have been affected by
the [virus, which is transmitted by mosquitoes. Rao said 273 medical
teams and 1219 paramedical teams were working in the districts to tackle
the epidemic. He said insecticides were being used in the affected
villages and that vaccines were being sent to the worst-affected districts
of Kurnool, Anantapur, Prakasam and Warangal.
Government data showed there were 984 cases of Japanese encephalitis,
including deaths, in Andhra Pradesh in all of 1997 and 524 cases, including
201 deaths, in 1998.
